What if we embraced life every single minute? What if we embraced every moment? What if we embraced not only the "good" emotions but also the "hard/bad" ones? How would life be and feel then?  I tried it today during my workout session. It should have been a "shorter" one today, with one video included that I knew was gonna be hard. So I decided to embrace the burn and the exhaustion without trying to avoid or complain about it. Just feeling all emotions and loving every single minute of the workout. Of course I did little breaks in between during the "hard" video, but I did every movement more consciously and more correctly. At the end I was so pumped and excited that I did an extra workout of 10 min HIIT (even though I didn't had to because it wasn't on my workout plan) and felt more energetic than the whole day. So my answer to the questions above is, life feels freaking hell more amazing, exciting and energetic if you take every emotion and embrace it. When you feel it fully instead of pushing it away because it feels uncomfortable at first. Have you tried it? to my amazing hike with one of my dearest friends  . I realized again on this day that a hike is such an easy comparison to life. If you want to go far, you have to take breaks and if you never give up you reach the top of the mountain. On this journey I thought many times that I couldn't make it, but I pushed harder after every break, telling myself I can do it and in the end I enjoyed such an amazing view from the top. So lesson learned.
